For example, only 16 out of 34 states have adopted laws requiring the presentation of a photo ID card.
However, the newly introduced rules will make it quite undeniably difficult to exercise the right to vote in 2012.
Democratic critics mainly talk about the bias of approved laws and consider them to be an obvious effort to influence the results of the 2012 elections in key states.
The report of the Brennan Centre in 2011 shows that the states where these laws were passed represent 171 of the 270 votes in the electoral body necessary for the victory in the presidential election.
It is too early to declare with certainty that these legislative changes at the level of the electoral system will have a significant impact on the outcome of the 2012 presidential election.
