The evidence is the existence of virtually all-powerful and in all states the ubiquitous lobby.
The result is a desperate situation in the field of corruption, providing mutual benefits, legislation, where virtually everything is reprehensible, but nothing is criminal.
In Germany, the situation is that the state ministries, due to the lack of funding, are giving draft laws to private law firms that are heavily related to industry.
These bills are then approved in the Bundestag.
All power does not come from the people like that, as the Western constitutions say, but from financially strong groups that prefer their own interests.
