Conclusion As in antiquity, the current company is based on a reckless preference for its own benefit, regardless of the social interest.
By its very nature, private capital is no longer able to understand and exercise social benefits.
The result is now, as then, an unprecedented decadence of elites without any effort to reform a deeper nature.
