Today's university students are not the only ones who are attacked for their opinions.
I don't remember ever dreaming about studying at Oxford University.
Both my father and my older brother studied at the university, which I thought was the world's largest headquarters of knowledge, a modern wined Greek symposium motivating two pillars of civilization, free thinking and tolerance.
